print("Preparation: Start by washing your hands thoroughly with soap and water.Place the chicken on a clean cutting board. Using a sharp knife, cut the chicken into desired pieces (breasts, thighs, wings, etc.). Be careful to avoid cross-contamination by using a separate cutting board for vegetables or other ingredients.Pre-cooking Hygiene: After cutting the chicken, wash your hands again thoroughly to remove any bacteria from handling raw chicken.Cooking Instructions: Preheat your oven to 325째F (163째C).Season the chicken pieces with salt, pepper, and any other desired spices or herbs.Place the seasoned chicken on a baking sheet or in a roasting pan.Cooking: Put the chicken in the preheated oven and cook for approximately 30 minutes. Note that cooking times may vary based on the size and thickness of the chicken pieces.Use a meat thermometer to check the internal temperature of the chicken. It should reach 165째F (75째C) to ensure it's fully cooked.Post-cooking Hygiene:While the chicken is cooking, wash your hands and clean any surfaces that came into contact with raw chicken.After the chicken is done cooking, let it rest for a few minutes before serving.Enjoy your deliciously cooked chicken!")